
[1]opprobrious

   OPPRO'BRIOUS, a. [See Opprobrium.]

   1. Reproachful and contemptuous; scurrilous; as opprobrious language;
   opprobrious words or terms.

   2. Blasted with infamy; despised; rendered hateful; as an opprobrious
   name.
